dya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Verdun","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: habitational name from any of several places in France called Verdun. The placename is probably of Gaulish origin, deriving from <i>ver(n)</i> ‘alder’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill, fortress’.","Spanish and Catalan: habitational name from Verdú in Catalonia (Spain), which has the same origin as the French name (see 1 above).","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Verdon  , a cognate of 1 above. This surname is very rare in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Virden","meanings":["English: probably a variant of   Verdun  ."]},{"name":"Verdon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Lucien, Marcel, Pierre, Renaud, Sylvie.","French: habitational name from (Le) Verdon, the name of several places in various parts of France, for example in Dordogne, Gironde, and Marne. Compare   Ferdon  .","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Verdun, the name of a fief in Vessey (Manche), France. Compare   Verdun  ."]},{"name":"Varden","meanings":["English: variant of   Verdun  ."]}]},{"name":"Bertram","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’ + <i>hramn</i> ‘raven’. Ravens were traditional symbols of wisdom in Germanic mythology; Odin was regularly accompanied by ravens called Hugin and Munin. This name was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain.  See also  Bertrand ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Bertram I de Verdun was born about 1040, in Saint-Martin-des-Champs, Manche, Normandy, France, his father, Godefroid de de Verdun II, was 45 and his mother, Doda von Henneberg, was 39. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Maude de Modena. He died about 1100, in Farnham Royal, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 62."},"et":{"about 1040–about 1100":"umbes 1040–umbes 1100","1040–1100":"1040–1100","1050–1076":"1050–1076","1050–Female":"1050–Surnud","1062–1129":"1062–1129","1065–1132":"1065–1132","0997–1069":"0997–1069","1002–1077":"1002–1077","about 1040":"umbes 1040","18 January 2022":"18 jaanuar 2022","1077":"1077","1132":"1132","1065":"1065","1076":"1076","21 December 1077":"21. detsember 1077","1062":"1062","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","1129":"1129","0997":"0997","Abt 1062":"umbes 1062","1069":"1069","1002":"1002","1100":"1100","about 1069":"umbes 1069","about 1100":"umbes 1100","Farnham Royal, South Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Farnham Royal, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Verdun, Rue de la Baie, Saint-Martin-des-Champs, Avranches, Manche, Normandy, France":"Saint-Martin-des-Champs, Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Bourne, Cambridgeshire, England":"Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1040–about 1100":"noin 1040–noin 1100","1040–1100":"1040–1100","1050–1076":"1050–1076","1050–Female":"1050–Kuollut","1062–1129":"1062–1129","1065–1132":"1065–1132","0997–1069":"0997–1069","1002–1077":"1002–1077","about 1040":"noin 1040","18 January 2022":"18. tammikuuta 2022","1077":"1077","1132":"1132","1065":"1065","1076":"1076","21 December 1077":"21. joulukuuta 1077","1062":"1062","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","1129":"1129","0997":"0997","Abt 1062":"noin 1062","1069":"1069","1002":"1002","1100":"1100","about 1069":"noin 1069","about 1100":"noin 1100","Farnham Royal, South Bucki